               <tr><td ><p>Introduction</p>
</td><td ><p>Interesting facts, examples or quotations that logically point to the subject.</p>
<p>(Can be considered as argumentation for the article to be written and read)</p>
</td></tr>
               <tr><td ><p>Situation/ Problem described</p>
</td><td ><p>Describe the situation when you faced the problem. And the problem itself.</p>
<p>Talk about existing trends/problems in this or that area.</p>
<p>You can ask a question (or two) that will be answered in the article.</p>
</td></tr>
               <tr><td ><p>Solution</p>
